The paper deals with data detection algorithms for wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of hardware impairments on the performance of these algorithms, which is relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm that achieves near-optimal performance with low computational complexity, which is a topic that falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
